    "body": "### Problem\n\nOpening (on nightly) and closing (both on 0.9.1 and nightly) floating windows is not possible when Command-line window (`|cmdwin|`) is active.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nTo test opening:\r\n- Create config file with the following content:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal open_floating_win = function()\r\n  vim.api.nvim_open_win(\r\n    vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false),\r\n    false,\r\n    { relative = 'editor', row = 0, col = 0, width = 20, height = 10 }\r\n  )\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<Space>o', open_floating_win)\r\n```\r\n- Open Neovim with that config file.\r\n- Type `q:` (should open Command-line window).\r\n- Type `<Space>o`. It throws an `E11: Invalid in command-line window;` error.\r\n\r\n**Note**: This works on Neovim 0.9.1. Seems to be the consequence of #23228 (cc @seandewar).\r\n\r\n------\r\nTo test closing:\r\n- Create config file with the following content:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal win_id = vim.api.nvim_open_win(\r\n  vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false),\r\n  false,\r\n  { relative = 'editor', row = 0, col = 0, width = 20, height = 10 }\r\n)\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<Space>c', function() vim.api.nvim_win_close(win_id, true) end)\r\n```\r\n- Open Neovim with that config file. Should have floating window pre-opened.\r\n- Type `q:` (should open Command-line window).\r\n- Type `<Space>c`. It throws an `E11: Invalid in command-line window;` error.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOpening (without setting focus) and closing floating windows with active Command-line window should be possible.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-709+gce56ad2ba and 0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have Neovim's floating windows\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.4.4-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
